The paper focuses on robotic grasping using depth and RGB information, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of neural networks for prediction suggests computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as likely sub-categories. The paper also involves designing an algorithm for robotic grasp operation, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
